    lifestyle: "Manjalpur lifestyle embodies aspirational hope. Mornings start early – factory shifts begin 6-7am, requiring 5am wake-ups. Breakfast is hurried, children to school, husband/wife to work. Afternoons (post 2pm) see wives managing households, children's tuition, shopping. Evenings (6-8pm) see families relaxing in shared community spaces – children playing in parks, parents chatting. Community bonds are strong because residents are collectively building the area. Weekends involve family time – short trips to Atladara Lake, window shopping at emerging centers, religious temple visits. Children's education is paramount – families invest heavily in school fees (often 20% of income). Savings mentality is strong – luxuries are limited, investments in property and education prioritized. Social life is community-centric – neighbors become friends, weddings and celebrations involve entire building. The lifestyle is characterized by hope and effort – residents aren't wealthy but are building dignity and opportunity for their children. There's palpable energy, less cynicism than metro cities, and genuine community feeling."
